%% 3.2.1 App Login (Guardian mobile) — sequence
%% POST /api/Account/Login + optional deviceToken (Firebase)
%% BR03: Guardian-only — app checks JWT Role claim after login (backend does not block role at Login today)

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Guardian as Guardian
    participant App as Mobile App
    participant AC as AccountController
    participant AS as AccountService
    participant JWT as JwtService
    participant Repo as IRepository User
    participant DB as SQL Server

    Guardian->>App: Open app — no valid stored token
    App->>App: Show Login screen (logo, email, password, eye toggle)

    Guardian->>App: Enter email/password → tap Login
    App->>App: Button loading state
    App->>AC: POST /api/Account/Login LoginDto (+ deviceToken)
    AC->>AS: LoginAsync(dto)
    AS->>Repo: Load user + Role
    Repo->>DB: SELECT
    AS->>AS: BCrypt verify
    AS->>JWT: GenerateToken
    JWT-->>AS: JWT
    AS-->>AC: LoginReponseDto
    AC-->>App: 200 + token

    alt Role is not guardian (decode JWT or call Me)
        App->>App: Toast: Account is not a guardian — clear token, stop
    else Guardian
        App->>App: Store JWT in secure storage; refresh FCM token if applicable
        App->>Guardian: Navigate to Home
    end
